{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"title":"Type Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)"],"title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"enum","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"symbol","title":"PIDFile","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","text":"PID File Lifecycle"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" detects stale PID files by checking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/PIDFile/remove(from:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Removes the PID file from the VM bundle directory."}],"fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"remove","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"from","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"URL","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation3URLV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile\/remove(from:)","title":"remove(from:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","role":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/PIDFile/write(to:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the current process’s PID to the VM bundle directory."}],"fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"write","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"URL","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation3URLV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile\/write(to:)","title":"write(to:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to:)","role":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/PIDFile":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Sp